    <mj-section css-class="mj_section" background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="             
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">BlackRock’s private markets platform</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.altdaily.co/email/images/an-dec-12-1.jpg" alt="BlackRock’s private markets platform" href="https://www.altdaily.co" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">BlackRock has become the first asset manager to <a href="https://pitchbook.com/news/articles/blackrock-first-to-launch-global-wealth-platform-under-revised-eltif-2-0" target="_blank">launch</a> a global evergreen private markets platform under the <a href="https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:32023R0606" target="_blank">ELTIF 2.0</a> framework. The platform is intended to provide investors in Europe with exposure to a diverse range of alternative assets. The platform will initially launch with two new funds, the BlackRock Private Equity Fund and the Multi-Alternative Growth Fund. The launch comes just a few days after BlackRock announced its <a href="https://pitchbook.com/news/articles/blackrock-hps-purchase-record-year-gp-consolidation" target="_blank">acquisition</a> of HPS Investment Partners.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <!-- Content sections -->
    <mj-section css-class="mj_section" background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="              
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">Nippon Life considers $8.2 bn acquisition</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.altdaily.co/email/images/an-dec-12-2.jpg" alt="Nippon Life considers $8.2 bn acquisition" href="https://www.altdaily.co" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4; filter: blur(5px);">
          Nippon Life Insurance Company is in <a href="https://pitchbook.com/news/articles/nippon-life-in-talks-to-acquire-resolution-life-for-8-2b" target="_blank">discussions</a> to acquire Resolution Life Group Holdings for $8.2 billion, potentially creating the largest insurance transaction by a Japanese company. Bermuda-based Resolution Life, currently valued at $10.6 billion, already has an existing relationship with Nippon Life, which holds a 23% stake in the company. This comes amid a robust period of Japanese investment activity, with private equity deals nearing a 10-year high. Blackstone, which established a strategic partnership with Resolution Life in 2022, is expected to maintain its investment management agreement if the acquisition proceeds.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
